TDD exercise complete. All 8 tests for Conway's Game of Life are implemented and passing:
- Empty input
- Single cell dies (underpopulation)
- Cell with 1 neighbor dies
- Cell with 2 neighbors survives
- Cell with 3 neighbors survives
- Cell with 4+ neighbors dies (overpopulation)
- Dead cell with 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)
- Negative coordinates handled correctly

Final implementation uses sparse representation (only living cells stored) and unified filter logic following Conway's rules.
